    <worksheet name='Question 1'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run>Q1 Explain the difference between a Tableau Dashboard and a Tableau Story Point. Give two healthcare-related use cases.

Dashboard:
- Single page with multiple charts, KPIs, filters.
- Purpose: Live exploration of data.
- Healthcare use case: ICU dashboard showing bed occupancy + patient vitals + doctor availability together.

Story Point/Story:  
- Sequence of dashboards like PowerPoint slides.
- Purpose: Tell story step by step to management.
- Healthcare use case: Slide 1: Monthly admission trend → Slide 2: Top 3 costliest departments → Slide 3: Recommendation to add beds.

</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
        <view>
          <datasources />
          <aggregation value='true' />
        </view>
        <style />
        <panes>
          <pane selection-relaxation-option='selection-relaxation-allow'>
            <view>
              <breakdown value='auto' />
            </view>
            <mark class='Automatic' />
          </pane>
        </panes>
        <rows />
        <cols />
      </table>
      <simple-id uuid='{0EB3A58D-F6C3-4CB4-94CC-C1C635281FC7}' />
    </worksheet>
    <worksheet name='Question 2'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontsize='12'>Q2 What are Actions in Tableau? Explain how Filter Action can help hospital management analyze patient data.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontsize='12'>Answer:</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontsize='12'>Actions in Tableau are interactive features that connect worksheets/dashboards. When we click/select data in Chart A, it triggers changes in Chart B.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontsize='12'>Filter Action: Most used action type. Clicking a bar/point in Chart A automatically filters Chart B to show only related data.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontsize='12'>Hospital use case: Click &apos;Cardiology&apos; in Department bar chart → Heatmap below filters to show only Cardiology monthly billing/patients. Helps management analyze 1 dept quickly without manual filters.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
        <view>
          <datasources />
          <aggregation value='true' />
        </view>
        <style />
        <panes>
          <pane selection-relaxation-option='selection-relaxation-allow'>
            <view>
              <breakdown value='auto' />
            </view>
            <mark class='Automatic' />
          </pane>
        </panes>
        <rows />
        <cols />
      </table>
      <simple-id uuid='{37208074-3451-40BE-8D41-C278CBE4094A}' />
    </worksheet>
    <worksheet name='Sheet 7'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='1'>Doctor Performance And Patient KPI Analysis</run>
            <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='1'>Task 1: Doctor Performance</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
        <view>
          <datasources>
